The global automated sample storage systems market is witnessing growth due to the increasing demand for efficient sample handling and storage solutions across various industries such as pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, and healthcare. The segmentation of the market by product type includes systems and reagents, with systems being the dominant segment owing to their widespread usage in research and clinical laboratories. Additionally, the application segmentation encompasses diverse areas such as drug discovery, clinical diagnostics, biobanking, and compound management, with drug discovery leading in terms of market share.

